    <p>
      Science always came easily to Alisha Ovide and she was always interested
      in health and studying the human body.
    </p>

    <p>
      She grew up watching her mother, Alexis Morgan, who worked as a certified
      nursing assistant (CNA) in the labor and delivery unit at Good Samaritan
      Hospital in Brockton, Mass.
    </p>

    <p>
      Ovide excelled in subjects like anatomy and physiology and psychology. But
      her aspirations toward healthcare were solidified when she attended a
      special advanced medical program at Harvard University as a high school
      student.
    </p>
